><BLOCKQUOTE
CLASS="ABSTRACT"
><DIV
CLASS="ABSTRACT"
><P
></P
><A
NAME="AEN208"
></A
><P
>This document tries to explain the most basic features of <ACRONYM
CLASS="ACRONYM"
>NTP</ACRONYM
>, and
to answer many frequently asked questions.  The intention is to help the
average user to get a quick start with the official implementation of <ACRONYM
CLASS="ACRONYM"
>NTP</ACRONYM
>.
Technical issues and mathematics are avoided where possible.  Instead the most
common questions are tried to be answered, enabling everybody to get a working
configuration.</P
><P
></P
></DIV
></BLOCKQUOTE
><TABLE
BORDER="0"
WIDTH="100%"
CELLSPACING="0"
CELLPADDING="0"
CLASS="EPIGRAPH"
><TR
><TD
WIDTH="45%"
>&nbsp;</TD
><TD
WIDTH="45%"
ALIGN="LEFT"
VALIGN="TOP"
><I
><P
>All we do here is invent games to pass the time.</P
></I
></TD
></TR
><TR
><TD
WIDTH="45%"
>&nbsp;</TD
><TD
WIDTH="45%"
ALIGN="RIGHT"
VALIGN="TOP"
><I
><SPAN
CLASS="ATTRIBUTION"
>John O' Donohue</SPAN
></I
></TD
></TR
></TABLE
><DIV
CLASS="SECT1"
><H1
CLASS="SECT1"
><A
NAME="S-META"
>1. About this Document</A
></H1
><BLOCKQUOTE
CLASS="ABSTRACT"
><DIV
CLASS="ABSTRACT"
><P
></P
><A
NAME="AEN217"
></A
><P
>This section tries to answer questions about the document
itself.  So we could call it <SPAN
CLASS="phrase"
><SPAN
CLASS="PHRASE"
>Meta-<ACRONYM
CLASS="ACRONYM"
>FAQ</ACRONYM
></SPAN
></SPAN
>.  If you like, you can
call it <SPAN
CLASS="phrase"
><SPAN
CLASS="PHRASE"
>preface</SPAN
></SPAN
> or <SPAN
CLASS="phrase"
><SPAN
CLASS="PHRASE"
>foreword</SPAN
></SPAN
> as
well.</P
><P
></P
></DIV
></BLOCKQUOTE
><P
>This document is intended for beginners as well as advanced users
that are looking for for advice.  However, basic skills in system
administration are required to enjoy this tour.  True experts on the subject
will probably prefer the original documentation that comes with the software,
or correct me where I'm wrong.</P
><P
>The impatient may want to go directly to the first section, <A
HREF="NTP-s-time.htm"
>Section 2</A
>, where fundamentals of timekeeping are discussed.  The
next section, <A
HREF="NTP-s-sw-clocks.htm"
>Section 3</A
>, introduces clocks that are
implemented using computers.  If you are reading sequentially, you should be
ready for the section that presents <ACRONYM
CLASS="ACRONYM"
>NTP</ACRONYM
> (<A
HREF="NTP-s-def.htm"
>Section 4</A
>).</P
><P
>At that point focus is moving from a more theoretical treatment of
the subject to practical aspects, starting with <A
HREF="NTP-s-algo.htm"
>Section 5</A
>.  Then
in <A
HREF="NTP-s-config.htm"
>Section 6</A
> we are going into practice, namely configuration
of the <ACRONYM
CLASS="ACRONYM"
>NTP</ACRONYM
> software.  The following section (<A
HREF="NTP-s-refclk.htm"
>Section 7</A
>) will
talk about <SPAN
CLASS="phrase"
><SPAN
CLASS="PHRASE"
>reference clock</SPAN
></SPAN
>s.</P
><P
>Real life is talked about in <A
HREF="NTP-s-trouble.htm"
>Section 8</A
> where
procedures, tips and tricks for troubleshooting are presented.  For the
curious, <A
HREF="NTP-s-related.htm"
>Section 9</A
> will provide further information and
references to such.  Finally, there is a <A
HREF="NTP-g-all.htm"
>glossary</A
>
with some terms explained.</P
><P
>Those who are still reading sequentially are asked to try some of the
numerous hyperlinks found not only at the top and bottom of each section.  If
you got lost, you can always to back to the beginning where the table of
contents is.</P
><DIV
CLASS="QANDASET"
